main event: A crew observed a stationary object resembling a balloon for 7 minutes on May 25, 1955.
interesting points: The observation was made 75 miles WNW of JM 2334 (Ohio), The source of the observation was a crew member, The report indicates that there was no follow-up investigation conducted, The object was classified under Air-Visual observation type, The description of the object closely aligns with that of a balloon.
sighted object: one stationary object resembling a balloon
